<h3>Where do I begin?</h3>
<p>Students who meet the <a href="http://beta.byui.edu/online/online-degree/prospective-students/qualifications">admission requirements</a> can <a href="http://beta.byui.edu/online/online-degree/prospective-students/application">apply</a> to be directly admitted into a online degree program. These students will start by taking the <a href="http://beta.byui.edu/online/online-degree/online-orientation-course">online orientation course</a>, a one credit course offered every block. This course prepares students to succeed online and charts a course to graduation. Pathway students who complete Academic Start do not need to take GS 111.</p>
